-- Playtex shareholders OK Energizer takeover
-- 
-- Thu Sep 27, 2007 12:17pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/27/us-playtex-energizer-idUSWNAS502020070927

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Playtex Products Inc PYX.N said on Thursday that its shareholders approved for the maker of sunscreen and tampons to be acquired by battery company Energizer Holdings Inc ( ENR.N ). 

 The company, whose brands include Banana Boat, Hawaiian Tropic and Wet Ones, sees the acquisition - valued at about $1.16 billion plus the assumption of debt - closing on or about October 1. Playtex was trading up 3 cents or .16 percent, at $18.28, while Energizer was down $1.45 or 1.3 percent, to $110.12 on the New York Stock Exchange at midday. (Reporting by  Martinne Geller )